# Unified vecinita-llm Modal app (ADR-037)

Vecinita has **two** Modal LLM deployables sharing volume **`llm-models`**:

| App | Role |
|-----|------|
| **`vecinita-llm`** | Prod ChatRAG / ingest — pinned model |
| **`vecinita-llm-playground`** | Playground list/pull + sandbox eval `model_id` reloads |

## Do

- Route **prod** LLM HTTP (chat, ingest/retag) through `VECINITA_MODAL_LLM_URL` +
  **`VECINITA_MODAL_PROXY_KEY`** (required on generate/warm/models; `/health` may stay open —
  RD-165).
- Route **playground** list/pull/sandbox eval through `VECINITA_MODAL_LLM_PLAYGROUND_URL`
  (TP-S010-27). ChatRAG must not use the playground URL.
- Use **one client surface** (`LlmClient`) for generate/stream/warm + list/pull — shared
  env/auth/timeout resolver in `shared-schemas` (RD-163, TP-S010-20). Do not maintain a
  parallel models-only HTTP client.
- Use **vLLM** for inference; **HuggingFace Hub** (`huggingface_hub.snapshot_download`) for
  `pull_model_job` / `stage_default_model` — not `ollama pull`.
- Keep API path aliases: `GET/POST /models/ollama` (FE compat). Rename modules/types/UI to
  playground/LLM — drop Ollama as the mental model (RD-166, TP-S010-19).
- Store weights on Modal volume **`llm-models`** only (both apps); manifest at
  `/models/manifest.json`.
- Gate catalog/list/pull to tags `resolve_hf_repo` accepts (RD-168).
- Use shared HF **`apply_chat_template`** in `packages/llm-client` (RD-167, TP-S010-24).
- Wire **real vLLM token streaming** into SSE (RD-164) — do not fake stream by word-chunking
  a completed reply.
- Pin prod to `qwen2.5:1.5b-instruct` / `Qwen/Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct` (RD-169, TP-S010-25).

## Do not

- Deploy or add routes to **`vecinita-ollama`** — deprecated; de-deployed.
- Add `VECINITA_MODAL_OLLAMA_URL` / `VECINITA_OLLAMA_MODEL_ID` to new DO specs or client
  fallbacks (RD-170, TP-S010-29).
- Assume vLLM can read Ollama blob cache — incompatible formats.
- Build a **provider ABC** / multi-provider plugin framework (RD-171) unless a second backend
  is explicitly reintroduced.
- Point ChatRAG at the playground app URL.

## Model switching

One vLLM engine per GPU class instance; changing `model_id` reloads the engine (~60–120s).
Use `/warm` before eval batches. Playground reloads must not stomp the **prod** app.

